
                  Redland RDF Application Framework Bindings

[1]Dave Beckett

Overview

   [2]Redland is a library that provides a high-level interface for the
   Resource Description Framework (RDF) allowing the RDF graph to be
   parsed from XML, stored, queried and manipulated. Redland implements
   each of the RDF concepts in its own class via an object based API,
   reflected into the language APIs, currently C#, Java, Perl, PHP,
   Obj-C, Python, Ruby and Tcl. Several classes providing functionality
   such as for parsers, storage are built as modules that can be loaded
   at compile or run-time as required.

   The redland-bindings package provides the higher level language APIs
   to Redland in the following languages.
     * [3]C#
     * [4]Java
     * [5]Obj-C
     * [6]Perl
     * [7]PHP
     * [8]Python
     * [9]Ruby
     * [10]Tcl

Sources and Binaries

   The packaged sources are available from
   [11]http://download.librdf.org/source/ (master site) and also from the
   [12]SourceForge site. The development Subversion sources can also be
   [13]browsed with ViewCV. Binary packages of redland bindings and
   related libraries are available from the [14]download site.

License

   This library is free software / open source software released under
   the LGPL (GPL) or Apache 2.0 licenses. See [15]LICENSE.html for full
   details.

Installation and Documentation

   See [16]INSTALL.html for general installation and configuration
   information and the language specific documents for installing the
   interfaces in the current available APIs: [17]C#, [18]Java, [19]Perl,
   [20]PHP, [21]Python, [22]Ruby or [23]Tcl.

Mailing Lists

   The [24]Redland mailing lists discuss the development and use of
   Redland and Raptor as well as future plans and announcement of
   releases.
